1:32:25.607 --> 1:32:28.374
D Company, move out!

1:32:28.376 --> 1:32:30.443
You all right, pal?

1:32:30.445 --> 1:32:32.077
Uh, where you from?

1:32:32.079 --> 1:32:33.346
He's probably got the wind up.

1:32:33.348 --> 1:32:34.481
Well, he's not one of ours.

1:32:34.483 --> 1:32:36.382
He's bloody soaked.

1:32:36.384 --> 1:32:39.218
Fuck it. Let's just pick
him up and take him with us.

1:32:39.220 --> 1:32:41.621
Have to find the Devons.

1:32:41.623 --> 1:32:44.524
- What's he saying?
- What's that, mate?

1:32:44.526 --> 1:32:46.659
The Devons.

1:32:46.661 --> 1:32:50.330
I have to find the Devons.

1:32:50.332 --> 1:32:52.332
We're the Devons.

1:32:55.604 --> 1:32:58.138
- You're the Devons?
- Yes, Corp.

1:33:00.174 --> 1:33:01.608
Why haven't you gone over?

1:33:01.610 --> 1:33:03.275
W-We're the second wave.

1:33:03.277 --> 1:33:05.110
They don't send us all at once.

1:33:05.112 --> 1:33:08.113
Yeah, we're D Company.
We spent the night digging in.

1:33:08.115 --> 1:33:09.616
We go last.

1:33:11.386 --> 1:33:13.085
Are you all right?

1:33:13.087 --> 1:33:15.455
Mackenzie.
Where's Colonel Mackenzie?

1:33:15.457 --> 1:33:17.557
Well, he's down at the line.

1:33:17.559 --> 1:33:19.191
- Which way?
- This way.

1:33:19.193 --> 1:33:21.293
We're headed up there now.

1:33:21.295 --> 1:33:23.295
Oy, steady on, mate.
Where you going?

1:33:44.619 --> 1:33:46.186
Move!

1:33:49.724 --> 1:33:51.426
Let me by!

1:33:55.296 --> 1:33:56.629
Let me through!

1:33:56.631 --> 1:34:00.900
Remember, follow
your platoon commander.

1:34:00.902 --> 1:34:03.636
Stay spread out
and watch for his orders.

1:34:03.638 --> 1:34:05.438
Where is
your commanding officer?

1:34:05.440 --> 1:34:07.239
He's in the holding pen.

1:34:07.241 --> 1:34:10.710
Raise your signal
flags or fire the signal flares

1:34:10.712 --> 1:34:13.346
when you've taken your section
of the Hun line.

1:34:13.348 --> 1:34:14.614
B Company, stand to.

1:34:14.616 --> 1:34:16.516
Now, listen and listen well.

1:34:16.518 --> 1:34:18.585
On the first mark,
A Company will advance.

1:34:18.587 --> 1:34:20.753
B Company will then move
to the front line.

1:34:20.755 --> 1:34:22.922
Sir, I have a message
from General Erinmore.

1:34:22.924 --> 1:34:24.289
Who the fuck are you?

1:34:24.291 --> 1:34:25.658
The attack has been called off.

1:34:25.660 --> 1:34:27.627
General Erinmore has
called off the attack.

1:34:27.629 --> 1:34:29.629
Balls, man.
We're about to go over.

1:34:29.631 --> 1:34:31.364
- We've got them on the run.
- You don't.

1:34:31.366 --> 1:34:32.498
Please don't
send your men over.

1:34:32.500 --> 1:34:33.766
Get out of the way, Corporal!

1:34:33.768 --> 1:34:35.401
These are direct orders
from army command!

1:34:35.403 --> 1:34:36.636
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?!

1:34:36.638 --> 1:34:39.539
Jesus Christ, man!
Go and see the captain!

1:34:39.541 --> 1:34:41.641
Now, I want us up there
quickly, you understand?

1:34:41.643 --> 1:34:43.376
Do you understand?!

1:34:43.378 --> 1:34:45.645
- Yes, sir!
- Two Mills bombs per man.

1:34:45.647 --> 1:34:48.246
NCOs collect flares
and signal flags.

1:34:48.248 --> 1:34:50.217
- Keep to your stations.
- Oy. Oy!

1:34:58.460 --> 1:35:01.527
Nine and ten section
at the ready!

1:35:01.529 --> 1:35:05.398
We will advance
on the first whistle blast.

1:35:05.400 --> 1:35:07.299
- 11 and 12...
- ...not slow down.

1:35:07.301 --> 1:35:09.602
The man next to you falls,
keep moving.

1:35:09.604 --> 1:35:11.638
Your orders are
to break the lines.

1:35:11.640 --> 1:35:13.271
Where is the captain?

1:35:13.273 --> 1:35:15.307
He's over there.

1:35:15.309 --> 1:35:16.576
Keep in your section formation.

1:35:16.578 --> 1:35:18.544
Sir! Sir!

1:35:18.546 --> 1:35:21.814
Captain, I have a message.

1:35:21.816 --> 1:35:23.816
This attack is called off.

1:35:23.818 --> 1:35:26.388
You have to stop.
You have to stop!

1:35:30.324 --> 1:35:32.290
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?

1:35:32.292 --> 1:35:34.261
Where is Mackenzie?!

1:36:01.489 --> 1:36:03.255
Get back! Back!

1:36:03.257 --> 1:36:05.024
Return to your sections! Back!

1:36:05.026 --> 1:36:06.592
Hold fast!

1:36:06.594 --> 1:36:08.728
Seven Platoon, one minute!

1:36:08.730 --> 1:36:12.331
Sir, I have orders
to stop this attack!

1:36:12.333 --> 1:36:13.366
What?

1:36:13.368 --> 1:36:15.601
Where is Colonel Mackenzie?!

1:36:15.603 --> 1:36:17.570
He's further up the line.

1:36:17.572 --> 1:36:19.338
- How far?
- 300 yards.

1:36:19.340 --> 1:36:21.040
He's in a cut-and-cover.

1:36:21.042 --> 1:36:23.743
You'll have to wait until
the first wave goes over.

1:36:23.745 --> 1:36:25.680
No. No, I can't.

1:36:33.555 --> 1:36:36.758
Seven Platoon, 30 seconds!

1:36:48.737 --> 1:36:50.636
You can't possibly
make it that way, man.

1:36:50.638 --> 1:36:52.574
Are you bloody insane?

1:36:56.578 --> 1:36:59.345
What the hell are you doing,
Lance Corporal?

1:36:59.347 --> 1:37:01.416
No. No, no, no, no!

1:38:03.511 --> 1:38:05.711
Into position!

1:38:05.713 --> 1:38:07.446
Get ready!

1:38:07.448 --> 1:38:09.684
- Colonel Mackenzie.
- He's in there.

1:38:11.452 --> 1:38:13.786
- Two minutes!
- Let me through!

1:38:13.788 --> 1:38:15.588
Hey. Hey!

1:38:15.590 --> 1:38:17.390
- Let me through!
- What the hell do you think you're doing?

1:38:17.392 --> 1:38:18.558
I have to get through!

1:38:18.560 --> 1:38:19.926
I have to see
Colonel Mackenzie.

1:38:19.928 --> 1:38:21.661
- What are you doing?
- I have to stop this attack.

1:38:21.663 --> 1:38:22.895
Colonel, we've seen flares.

1:38:22.897 --> 1:38:25.464
The men on the left flank have
made it to the German line.

1:38:25.466 --> 1:38:27.600
- Colonel! Colonel!
- Hold him. Hold him.

1:38:27.602 --> 1:38:29.836
Listen to me. Listen to me.
I have a letter.

1:38:29.838 --> 1:38:31.671
I need to see
Colonel Mackenzie!

1:38:31.673 --> 1:38:33.606
There's no bloody way
you're getting in there, mate.

1:38:33.608 --> 1:38:34.740
Sergeant, send the next wave.

1:38:34.742 --> 1:38:36.409
No!

1:38:36.411 --> 1:38:38.511
Second wave,
prepare yourselves!

1:38:38.513 --> 1:38:40.513
- Colonel Mackenzie!
- Concentrate everything there.

1:38:40.515 --> 1:38:42.615
This attack is not to go ahead!

1:38:42.617 --> 1:38:45.618
You have been ordered to stop.
You have to stop.

1:38:45.620 --> 1:38:47.486
Who the hell are you?

1:38:47.488 --> 1:38:49.755
Lance Corporal Schofield,
sir, 8th.

1:38:49.757 --> 1:38:51.490
I have orders from
General Erinmore

1:38:51.492 --> 1:38:52.625
to call off this attack.

1:38:52.627 --> 1:38:53.993
You're too late,
Lance Corporal.

1:38:53.995 --> 1:38:56.028
Sir, these orders
are from army command.

1:38:56.030 --> 1:38:57.630
You have to read them.

1:38:57.632 --> 1:38:59.432
Shall we hold back
the second wave, sir?

1:38:59.434 --> 1:39:00.733
No, Major.
Hesitate now, and we lose.

1:39:00.735 --> 1:39:02.501
Victory's only 500 yards away.

1:39:02.503 --> 1:39:04.437
Sir, please read the letter.

1:39:04.439 --> 1:39:07.440
I have heard it all before.

1:39:07.442 --> 1:39:09.508
I'm not going to wait
until dusk or for fog.

1:39:09.510 --> 1:39:10.810
I'm not calling back my men

1:39:10.812 --> 1:39:12.478
only to send them
out there again tomorrow,

1:39:12.480 --> 1:39:13.880
not when we've got
the bastards on the run.

1:39:13.882 --> 1:39:15.514
This is their last stand.

1:39:15.516 --> 1:39:17.950
The Germans planned this, sir.

1:39:17.952 --> 1:39:19.752
They've been planning it
for months.

1:39:19.754 --> 1:39:22.655
They want you to attack.

1:39:22.657 --> 1:39:24.592
Read the letter.

1:39:44.545 --> 1:39:46.514
- Major?
- Yes, sir?

1:39:48.816 --> 1:39:51.550
- Stand them down.
- Yes, sir.

1:39:51.552 --> 1:39:53.686
Call up the
orderlies. Tend the wounded.

1:39:53.688 --> 1:39:55.488
Hold the line
in case they counter.

1:39:55.490 --> 1:39:56.923
Yes, sir.

1:39:56.925 --> 1:40:00.526
Stand down! Stand down!

1:40:02.263 --> 1:40:03.596
Stand down!

1:40:05.733 --> 1:40:08.935
- Cease fire! Cease fire!
- Stand down!

1:40:12.974 --> 1:40:15.576
I hoped today might be
a good day.

1:40:17.845 --> 1:40:20.048
Hope is a dangerous thing.

1:40:21.783 --> 1:40:23.683
That's it for now,
and then next week,

1:40:23.685 --> 1:40:26.719
command will send
a different message.

1:40:26.721 --> 1:40:28.656
"Attack at dawn."

1:40:31.759 --> 1:40:33.861
There is only one way
this war ends.

1:40:36.297 --> 1:40:38.466
Last man standing.

1:40:43.738 --> 1:40:45.707
Have someone
see to your wounds.

1:40:48.609 --> 1:40:50.845
Now fuck off, Lance Corporal.

1:40:56.617 --> 1:40:57.817
Bearers!

1:40:57.819 --> 1:41:00.786
Stretcher bearers!

1:41:00.788 --> 1:41:02.555
Bearers!

1:41:02.557 --> 1:41:04.557
Stretcher bearers!

1:41:04.559 --> 1:41:06.959
Well done, lad.

1:41:06.961 --> 1:41:08.629
Thank you, sir.

1:41:10.698 --> 1:41:12.965
Do you know where
Lieutenant Blake is, sir?

1:41:12.967 --> 1:41:14.767
Blake?

1:41:14.769 --> 1:41:16.669
There were two of us.

1:41:16.671 --> 1:41:18.971
I was sent here
with his brother.

1:41:18.973 --> 1:41:21.040
Ah.

1:41:21.042 --> 1:41:22.842
Well, knowing Lieutenant Blake,

1:41:22.844 --> 1:41:24.777
he would have gone over
with his men.

1:41:24.779 --> 1:41:27.913
He was in the first wave.

1:41:27.915 --> 1:41:29.782
How could I find him, sir?

1:41:29.784 --> 1:41:31.984
You can try
the casualty clearing station

1:41:31.986 --> 1:41:34.854
behind the line.

1:41:34.856 --> 1:41:36.557
Otherwise...

1:41:39.627 --> 1:41:41.060
Thank you, sir.

1:41:41.062 --> 1:41:43.062
Major Hepburn, sir.

1:41:50.838 --> 1:41:52.807
- Keep moving. Keep moving.
- Nearly there.

1:42:03.618 --> 1:42:04.952
Ow!

1:42:07.655 --> 1:42:08.723
Will I make it?

1:42:11.025 --> 1:42:12.860
Will I make it?

1:42:17.065 --> 1:42:19.732
- Go the fuck up.
- Clear the way.

1:42:19.734 --> 1:42:21.167
Come on, quickly.

1:42:21.169 --> 1:42:23.169
Get a medic!

1:42:23.171 --> 1:42:26.707
Medic! Medic!

1:42:34.048 --> 1:42:35.147
Just keep moving.

1:42:35.149 --> 1:42:37.083
Keep moving, keep moving.

1:42:37.085 --> 1:42:38.851
That's it.

1:43:02.677 --> 1:43:04.944
Sergeant, I have to find
Lieutenant Blake.

1:43:04.946 --> 1:43:06.881
- Do you know where he is?
- No.

1:43:11.686 --> 1:43:13.018
Make way for the stretchers!

1:43:13.020 --> 1:43:14.720
Minor injuries
to the far field.

1:43:14.722 --> 1:43:16.155
Stretchers to me.

1:43:16.157 --> 1:43:18.757
Walking wounded
to the collection area.

1:43:18.759 --> 1:43:21.160
Move aside to let
the stretcher bearers through.

1:43:25.733 --> 1:43:27.668
- Move it.
- Clear the way.

1:43:28.803 --> 1:43:30.970
Sir, is Lieutenant Blake here?

1:43:30.972 --> 1:43:33.239
No idea.

1:43:33.241 --> 1:43:36.175
Move along, Corporal.

1:43:36.177 --> 1:43:38.978
If you can walk,
move to the triage area.

1:43:38.980 --> 1:43:40.779
I can't move.

1:43:40.781 --> 1:43:41.983
Help me.

1:43:44.752 --> 1:43:46.018
Let me go home.

1:43:46.020 --> 1:43:47.286
Lieutenant Blake!

1:43:47.288 --> 1:43:49.223
I need an M.O. over here.

1:43:52.727 --> 1:43:54.126
Sir, he's out.

1:43:54.128 --> 1:43:56.929
Get him out of here, now.

1:43:56.931 --> 1:43:59.999
Out of the bloody way.

1:44:00.001 --> 1:44:02.134
Blake?!

1:44:02.136 --> 1:44:03.802
Out of the way!

1:44:03.804 --> 1:44:05.873
Has anyone seen
Lieutenant Blake?!

1:44:07.775 --> 1:44:08.908
He's hemorrhaging.
Go quickly.

1:44:08.910 --> 1:44:10.910
He needs a surgeon.

1:44:10.912 --> 1:44:13.946
I want to be left here.

1:44:13.948 --> 1:44:16.315
Tourniquet!

1:44:16.317 --> 1:44:18.217
- Don't look. It's okay.
- Amputation.

1:44:18.219 --> 1:44:20.119
Straight to surgery.

1:44:21.956 --> 1:44:25.159
My leg! My leg.

1:44:28.296 --> 1:44:30.229
I need some help here, quickly!

1:44:30.231 --> 1:44:31.830
He's gone.

1:44:31.832 --> 1:44:34.099
I can't die.

1:44:34.101 --> 1:44:36.101
Don't let me fucking die.

1:44:36.103 --> 1:44:38.239
- I need something now!
- I need my mum.

1:44:40.942 --> 1:44:42.143
Coming through.

1:44:56.090 --> 1:44:58.224
All right, come on, boys.

1:44:58.226 --> 1:45:00.125
He's taken one in the leg.

1:45:00.127 --> 1:45:02.127
- He's lost a lot of blood.
- Sir.

1:45:02.129 --> 1:45:03.563
Lieutenant Blake?

1:45:03.565 --> 1:45:06.198
Yes?

1:45:06.200 --> 1:45:09.268
Do you need medical assistance?

1:45:09.270 --> 1:45:11.070
No, sir.

1:45:11.072 --> 1:45:12.372
I'm from the 8th.

1:45:12.374 --> 1:45:15.007
What the hell
are you doing here?

1:45:15.009 --> 1:45:16.875
I was sent here
to deliver a message.

1:45:16.877 --> 1:45:18.077
The 8th?

1:45:18.079 --> 1:45:20.846
You must know my brother.

1:45:20.848 --> 1:45:22.181
I was sent here with him.

1:45:22.183 --> 1:45:24.151
Tom's here? Where is he?

1:45:30.425 --> 1:45:32.361
It was very quick.

1:45:34.429 --> 1:45:36.130
I'm sorry.

1:45:59.987 --> 1:46:02.121
What's your name?

1:46:02.123 --> 1:46:04.058
Schofield, sir.

1:46:06.927 --> 1:46:08.994
I'm sorry, what?

1:46:08.996 --> 1:46:10.863
It's Schofield, sir.

1:46:10.865 --> 1:46:13.299
William Schofield.

1:46:13.301 --> 1:46:14.869
Will.

1:46:16.937 --> 1:46:18.304
Well, you need some food.

1:46:18.306 --> 1:46:20.241
Get yourself to the mess tent.

1:46:35.022 --> 1:46:39.925
If I may, I'd like
to write to your mother.

1:46:39.927 --> 1:46:41.862
Tell her that Tom wasn't alone.

1:46:44.499 --> 1:46:46.435
Of course.

1:46:49.136 --> 1:46:51.970
He was...

1:46:51.972 --> 1:46:53.841
He was a good man.

1:46:55.677 --> 1:46:57.845
Always telling funny stories.

1:47:00.382 --> 1:47:02.351
He saved my life.

1:47:06.120 --> 1:47:08.089
I am glad you were with him.

1:47:14.128 --> 1:47:16.063
Thank you, Will.
